The error is due to the attempt to concatenate a string with a number, whic
which Tundra does not support. We need to convert the price and fee from st
strings to numbers before performing the addition operation. Here's how we 
can fix this program:

```Tundra
def parseNumber(str) {
    var i = 0;
    while (i < str.length && ((str[i] < '0' || str[i] > '9') && str[i] != '
'-')) {
        i += 1;
    }
    
    if (i == str.length) {
      return 0;
    } else {
        var negative = false;
        if (str[i] == '-') {
            negative = true;
            i += 1;
        }
        
        var num = 0;
        while (i < str.length && str[i] >= '0' && str[i] <= '9') {
            num *= 10;
            num += parseInt(str[i]);
            i += 1;
        }
        
        return negative ? -num : num;
    }
}

def normalize(raw)  {
  return {
    price: raw.price,
    fee: parseNumber(raw.fee)
   };
}

val raw = {
  price: "18",
  fee: "2"
};

val item = normalize(raw);
val total = item.price + item.fee;

print(total);
```
This code first defines a parseNumber function, which can convert strings t
to numbers by iterating through the string and building up an integer value
value from its characters. This is essentially reimplementing JavaScript's 
built-in `parseInt` functionality in Tundra. Then it normalizes the raw dat
data into a price and fee, adds them together, and prints out the result.
